Had the same problem. Seems that at some moment (update of mods etc.) some parts get an empty "category" tag in the part.cfg. You can fix that by editing (for example the intakes) "category = Aero" in every concerned part.cfg. After that and a restart of ksp you will find this part in this category of the VAB.

The problem seems is that you play without a techtree. The game is desigined to play either with the clasic KSPI techtree or the new CTT techtree. If you don't play with either one, you might find that parts are missing all together because you are not supposed to get access to them without additional technodes. That's because KSPI parts are significantly more advanced and therefore require additional research Edited March 4, 2015 by FreeThinker

FYI, the "-master" is a GitHub thing, it means the repository you are grabbing is the "master" branch, since people make all sorts of tweaks etc, and they want to test them, or have other people test them, they need to differentiate between off-shoot branches of any particular bit of code and the (hopefully) bug-free master branch. Just rename the folder (once unzipped) to the same name without the "-master" on the end before merging it into your gamedata folder in KSP. (This is common to many, many mod-ready games. Now you know.

Hello,

There is a typo in one of the Module names for several reactors...I dont know what the extended version is trying to do but I will tell you that extneded version only adds another tweakable part (and then only on some cases) and changes no data; tweaking the parts will not effect a data change either unless somehting like this is used:

TWEAKSCALEEXPONENTS

{

name = InterstellarFissionPBDPsmall

radius = 1

PowerOutput = 3

.2

upgradedPowerOutput = 3

.2

partMass = 2.5

}

I dont know if the many efficincy ratings are changed; probly not and are of no consequence except for resizing the part; the purpose of TweakScale is to save space on parts but if rate changes are not effected as well there is no use. It's best use is in multiple storage units (so far for me) and solving VAB part bugs which I have yet to finish as I am working on that tonite (live on stream as usual !).

The problem is rescaling is changing resource values by X8; with nuclear components I think it is a tadd overkill; my other thinking was to choose my favorite nuclear power and go with it: fusion; that and Thermal; I can save some game memory space that way; I dont understand the uses of the reactors yet but Youtube helps I found some good tutorials.

So now it is on to try and add Interstellar lite parts...just chekin...their DLL is called InterstellarPlugin.DLL of all things and they changed the directory; they added new parts and possibly new modules but I am checking; I dont know yet if I can add both.
